  "description": [
    "THE BROWNING CHIEF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July 15 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Montana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance THE MEANING OF THE TRUCE If the truce terms outlined by the Peiping radio are authentic they will have to be sharply modified Evacuation of foreign troops as soon as possible is the key question The Commun ists must be told at once that it will be impossible to remove all United Nations forces any time soon They may ask for the sta tus quo restorationbefore June 25 1950 but they wont get it This time genuine insurance against a repetition of aggress ion must be had No Communist promises will provide it The security of the Republic of Korea must be safe guarded by maintaining both the means to repel invasion and to sound an advance alarm Mut ual withdrawals or buffer zones can facilitate a measure of evacu ation But strong UN forces must remain until South Korean armies are trained and equipped And effective inspection systems must be established to make sure"
  ],
